System 1:
  Get the ip: ipconfig (Copy ipv4)
  Open Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security
    Click Inbound Rules (left panel) -> New Rule... (right panel).
    Select Port -> Next.
    Select TCP and enter these exact ports: 3000, 7545, 8080    
    Select Allow the connection -> Next.
    Check all profiles (Domain, Private, Public) -> Next.

  Ganache:
    Open Ganache UI, click the Gear Icon (Settings), and go to the Server tab.
    Change the Hostname dropdown to 0.0.0.0 - All Interfaces (or select your specific 192.168.1.92 address).  
    Click Save and Restart.

  IPFS:
    Open a Command Prompt and run these two commands to open your IPFS nodes to the network:
    ipfs config Addresses.API /ip4/0.0.0.0/tcp/5001
    ipfs config Addresses.Gateway /ip4/0.0.0.0/tcp/8080

  In HTML:
    const IPFS_GATEWAY = "http://Sytstem_1_IP:8080/ipfs/";

System 2: 
  Configure MetaMask:
    Go to Add Network -> Add a network manually.
    Network Name: ISRO Local Ledger
    New RPC URL: http://System_1_IP:7545
    Chain ID: 1337
    Currency Symbol: ETH
    Save and switch to this network.

  Open your web browser and type the web server address into the URL bar: http://System_1_IP:3000
